The paper discusses a novel indexing scheme and querying approach for natural language text corpora that are available as sets of syntactically parsed trees. This involves searching for roles and relationships within sentences, which is a common task in information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed indexing scheme and coding scheme are designed to improve querying performance, which is a key concern in database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper also discusses the potential for improved search effectiveness, which is a common goal in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
